text: Tobermory (Scottish Gaelic: Tobar Mhoire) is a town on the Isle of Mull in Scotland. It has roughly around 1,000 people. Historically the town was a fishing port. Tobermory is well known for hosting the children's television show Balamory. == References == Category:Towns in Argyll and Bute Category:Port cities and towns of Scotland
title: Tobermory, Mull
